Admission Requirements:
Academic Qualifications: Prospective students are required to meet the academic requirements specific to their chosen program of study. This may include submitting transcripts, standardized test scores, and letters of recommendation.

Language Proficiency: Since the medium of instruction at UWM is predominantly Polish or English, depending on the program, proficiency in the respective language is essential. Applicants may need to demonstrate their language proficiency through standardized tests such as the TOEFL or IELTS.

